Time slots for the examination on Monday, 22nd of July:

Examination is in presence and will take place in MS 107 . Please be there at least 10 minutes in advance before your time slot begins. Please, upload your final presentation on ISIS before your exam, we will download it from there to the local computer. A back-up usb stick might be a good idea.

Time slots for the Second intermediate presentation on Monday, 15th of July, are:

It is the last presentation before the exam. We ask each group to create a 15-minutes presentation that contains the results of a completed project. Please, consider it as a tryout for your final presentation. It means that:
You have to be perfect with time;
You should show the most interesting/important/key parts of your project (e.g., don't explain the BC for a single element test for 10 minutes);
Please consider our comments on the first intermediate presentation.
After each presentation, we will give you our feedback and comments, which would be nice to implement before the exam (and maybe even in the report!).
As before, not everyone from the group has to present: one or two persons would be enough. And, please, join
time slots and not just the one for your group!
